      "cr": 10,
      "type": {
        "value": "dragon"
      },
      "alignment": "unaligned",
      "biography": {
        "value": "\n                        Legends speak of elemental plains where condiments flow like rivers and dragons feast on pure flavor. The Condiment Drake is believed to be a rare offspring of these planes, driven to the material world by an insatiable hunger for the ultimate taste. They hoard not gold, but rare spices, aged vinegars, and artisanal salts, viewing them as treasures of immense value.\n                        <hr>\n                        <p><strong>Behavior:</strong> The Condiment Drake is territorial and aggressive, fiercely defending its hoard of rare spices and exotic sauces. It often uses its breath weapon to incapacitate intruders before finishing them off with its claws and tail.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Appearance:</strong> This medium-sized dragon resembles a terrestrial dragon but with a leathery hide in shades of deep red, vibrant yellow, and mottled green. Its scales glisten as if perpetually coated in sauce, and its eyes are small, black, and beady like peppercorns. A faint, tangy aroma surrounds it.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Twist:</strong> Despite its aggressive nature, the Condiment Drake possesses an uncanny ability to perfectly season any food it encounters, making it a bizarrely sought-after culinary ingredient by those brave or foolish enough to hunt one.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Found near ancient spice routes, forgotten pantries, or areas with unusually rich soil that grows potent herbs.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Treasure:</strong> None</p>\n                    "
      },
